 to the challenges of multiculturalism, the relationship between the state and religion, the struggle for political legitimacy, and the capabilities approach. Extending Rawls's progressive thought to the fields of law, economics, and public reason, this book helps advance the project of a free society that thrives despite disagreements over religious and moral views.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aLiberalismxPhilosophy 0aLiberalismxPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aBrooks, Thom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrooks, Thom, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMichelman, Frank I., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNussbaum, Martha C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNussbaum, Martha C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aO’Neill, Onora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWaldron, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWeithman, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311066586440uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/broo1497040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231527729423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231527729.jpg  a978-3-11-066586-4  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles